Definition: the readiness to perceive sensations
Example: elementary or undifferentiated consciousness; gave sentience to slugs and newts- Richard Eberhart
Synonyms: adj, all, conscious, sentient, insentience, animateness, the, readiness, to, perceive, sensations, elementary, or, undifferentiated, consciousness, gave, slugs, and, newts, -, Richard, Eberhart
Category: noun.attribute
